result.execSummary:
The defendant Zaxyz L Kimmel was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possess Drug Paraphernalia, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.573(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Costs to be paid directly to the Waushara County Clerk of Court within 60 days or establish a payment plan.  Failure to pay may result in suspension of your driver's license, tax intercept, a civil judgment being entered against you, a warrant being issued for your arrest for contempt and/or the debt being turned over to a collection agency.

1:38 pm case called. Defendant Zaxyz L Kimmel in court with attorney Ben Szilagyi.  Defendant Zaxyz L Kimmel in custody.  Scott C. Blader appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Personal appearance waived by the defendant.   Complaint Stated - Advised of offense and minimum/maximum penalty.  Receipt Admitted - Reading Waived. Defendant advised of right to counsel and expertise.  Voluntary waiver of counsel accepted by Court.  Defendant advised of minimum/maximum penalty.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained. Chapter 950 compliance addressed. Plea: No Contest.   Court accepts plea and enters JOC. Court sentences the defendant to: 1 day WCJ, with 1 day credit for time served. Costs to be paid within 60 days or payment plan. Appeal Rights faxed to WCJ for signature.
